memberdef.initializer: = new XLRangeAddress( new XLAddress(-1, -1, fixedRow: true, fixedColumn: true), new XLAddress(-1, -1, fixedRow: true, fixedColumn: true) )

briefdescription.para: Lead a range address to a normal form - when FirstAddress points to the top-left address and LastAddress points to the bottom-right address.
Determines whether range address spans the entire column.

simplesect.para: true if is entire column; otherwise, false.

briefdescription.para: Determines whether range address spans the entire row.

simplesect.para: true if is entire row; otherwise, false.

briefdescription.para: Determines whether the range address spans the entire worksheet.

simplesect.para: true if is entire sheet; otherwise, false.

briefdescription.para: Returns a range address so that its offset from the target base address is equal to the offset of the current range address to the source base address. For example, if the current range address is D4:E4, the source base address is A1:C3, then the relative address to the target base address B10:D13 is E14:F14
Returns the intersection of this range address with another range address on the same worksheet.
Allocates the current range address in the internal range repository and returns it
